definition.value: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate having xanthosine as the nucleobase.
The xanthosine 5'-phosphate in which the 5'-phosphate is a triphosphate group.

A member of the class of diazepanones that is 1,3-diazepane which is substituted by a 3-(1,3-thiazol-2-ylcarbamoyl)benzyl group at positions 1 and 3, oxo group at position 2, hydroxy groups at positions 5S and 6S, and benzyl groups at positions 4R and 7R. It is a potent HIV-1 protease inhibitor.
